14 WHEREAS, he has also delivered several lectures at colleges and universities, written about
15 social justice topics for publications such as Billboard, and been the subject of multiple
16 interviews regarding police misconduct and race relations; and
17 WHEREAS, his presence in televised media includes his own Emmy Award-winning show
18 Love and Respect, cameos on Ozark and Billions, and regular appearances on the Late Show
19 with Stephen Colbert and Real Time with Bill Maher; and
20 WHEREAS, the documentary series Trigger Warning with Killer Mike, in which he explores
21 issues in the United States that affect the black community, premiered on Netflix in January
22 2019; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
24 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately honored.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize and commend Michael S. "Killer Mike" Render for his many exemplary
27 contributions on behalf of the citizens of this state and beyond as well as extend their best
28 wishes for continued success.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Michael S. "Killer
31 Mike" Render.
